[14:16:29] {"event": "tool_call", "tool": "think", "args": {"thought": "\nAnalyzing the 3 distinct failures:\n\n**Failure 1 & 5: TC-83232 Newsletter (Chromium + Edge)**\n- Error: `locator('div.bg-primary input[type=\"email\"]').first()` times out at line 414\n- But the test code at lines 413-453 (the current code in the file) shows the UPDATED version with retry loops and 45s timeout — and the error points to line 414 which says `await homePage.newsletterEmailInput.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 30_000 });`\n- Wait - line 414 in the error shows `await homePage.newsletterEmailInput.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 30_000 });` but the current code at line 452 shows `await homePage.newsletterEmailInput.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 45_000 });`\n- This suggests the error log was from a PREVIOUS version of the code. The current code in `home-page.spec.ts` at line 452 shows 45_000 timeout.\n- Actually wait - looking at line 414 in the current file: the error context shows line 414 with `await homePage.newsletterEmailInput.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 30_000 });` - but the current file at line 452 shows `timeout: 45_000`. This means either:\n  1. The error log was captured from old code, OR\n  2. The file was updated after the test run\n\nLooking at the git status: `tests/home-page.spec.ts (M)` - it's modified. So the test was updated after the run. But the error was `TimeoutError: locator.waitFor: Timeout 30000ms exceeded` which means the OLD code had 30_000.\n\nThe current code already has 45_000 and retry loops. The issue is: does the newsletter element EVER appear on Chromium/Edge? The element `div.bg-primary input[type=\"email\"]` may simply not be rendered on those browsers, or the class might have changed.\n\n**Root cause hypothesis for TC-83232:**\nThe newsletter section is Builder.io-driven. The locator `div.bg-primary input[type=\"email\"]` might not match because:\n1. The `bg-primary` class element might not exist at all (Builder.io may render differently per browser)\n2. The element might exist but with a different class hierarchy\n\n**Failure 2 & 6: TC-83240 Login (Chromium + Edge)**\n- Error: `locator('input[name=\"email\"][type=\"email\"]').first()` timeout 15000ms\n- The LoginPage.ts at line 28 shows `timeout: 15_000` but the current file shows `timeout: 45_000`\n- Again, git shows `pages/LoginPage.ts (M)` - file was modified after the run\n- The current code navigates to `/auth/login` directly and has 45_000 timeout, networkidle wait, and body click\n\n**Failure 3 & 4: TC-83238 In-Store Pickup (Firefox + WebKit)**\n- Error: `locator('p.cursor-pointer.text-primary').filter({ hasText: /set your store/i }).first()` timeout 15000ms\n- The `ProductDetailPage.ts` is also modified (git status shows M)\n- The current code at `openStoreSelectorDialog()` (lines 270-306) has been significantly updated with the scroll + wait + fallback logic\n- The error points to `ProductDetailPage.ts:262` but current file line 262 is in the middle of the updated `openStoreSelectorDialog()` method\n- Current code: `await this.setYourStoreLink.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 5_000 })` at line 292 (try/catch) - this is the short 5_000 timeout used before falling back to \"check availability\" link\n\nSo the current code in all files has already been updated compared to what was reported in the error. The question is: are these fixes sufficient, or do we need to investigate further?\n\nGiven that:\n1. All files are already modified (M in git status)\n2. The error timeouts shown (30_000, 15_000, 15_000) don't match current code timeouts (45_000, 45_000, 5_000/15_000)\n3. The current code has improved retry logic\n\nThe \"Additional Instructions\" says \"Fix this issues\" - meaning they want me to fix them NOW based on the current error report.\n\nLet me re-read the error more carefully:\n\nFor TC-83232: The error trace shows line 414 `await homePage.newsletterEmailInput.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 30_000 });`. The current home-page.spec.ts has significant retry logic and 45_000. But the error says it failed at what WAS line 414. The current spec line 452 does: `await homePage.newsletterEmailInput.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 45_000 });`. That's already been updated.\n\nHmm, but the playlist context says \"Fix this issues\" with the current failures. Maybe the current code changes haven't been tested yet and I need to verify them, OR maybe the issues persist.\n\nSince the task at hand is the framework-exploration skill AND I need to fix these issues, I should:\n1. Complete the framework exploration (create FRAMEWORK-SPEC and FRAMEWORK-AUDIT files)\n2. Fix the 3 distinct failures if the current code doesn't already address them\n\nLooking at the current code:\n- TC-83232: Already has retry loop + 45s timeout. BUT the core issue might be the selector `div.bg-primary input[type=\"email\"]` not matching. Need to verify via browser.\n- TC-83240: Already navigates to `/auth/login` with 45s timeout. \n- TC-83238: Already has fallback logic for Firefox/WebKit.\n\nThe problem is I can't run the tests right now to verify. But looking at the error patterns:\n\nFor TC-83238 specifically: Firefox/WebKit fail because the geolocation API is likely auto-detecting a store (replacing \"Set your store\" with \"Check availability at other stores\"). The current code handles this via try/catch fallback. However, the error shows `Timeout 15000ms` on `setYourStoreLink.waitFor` - that's the OLD code. The current code has `timeout: 5_000` in the try block and falls back. This should be better.\n\nFor TC-83232: The newsletter section may not render at all on some browsers. The locator might need to be more flexible or we need a different approach.\n\nFor TC-83240: The login navigates to `/auth/login` but uses `waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 15_000 })` in the error - old code. Current has 45_000.\n\nSince all pages have already been updated (M in git status), the test run shown in \"Additional Instructions\" was from BEFORE those updates. The current code may already fix these issues.\n\nHowever, I still need to:\n1. Run the framework-exploration skill to produce the required outputs\n2. Address the specific test failures if the current code still needs adjustments\n\nLet me focus on:\n1. Examining what specifically might still be wrong with the current code\n2. Making any necessary fixes\n3. Writing the FRAMEWORK-SPEC and FRAMEWORK-AUDIT\n\nFor the TC-83232 newsletter issue - the most likely remaining problem is that `div.bg-primary input[type=\"email\"]` selector might not match. Let me check if there's a more robust approach needed.\n\nActually, the key insight is: I need to use the browser to check if these selectors actually work. But I should also look at what the test result error context files say.\n"}}
